"help.formats_title" = "Formats & limits";
"help.formats_body" = "LatZip uses the system libarchive for listing and extraction. It works well with ZIP, TAR, 7z, RAR (depending on build), ISO 9660, CPIO, AR, CAB, LHA/LZH, XAR, DEB, WARC, and common compressions (gzip, bzip2, xz, zstd, lzma, Unix .Z).\n\nDisk images and raw volumes (DMG, VMDK, QCOW2, NTFS/APFS as whole disks, etc.) are not opened as “archives” by libarchive. If something does not open, the format likely needs another tool.\n\n“Protect with password” rewrites only .zip files with WinZip-style AES-256 when your libarchive supports it.";
